      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09B_temp` for records where the tour starts with `J09B`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09B_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type:\\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`\\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`\\n\\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`. Join with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use net data customer table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09B`. Use these column names when exporting:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached. Use `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_ba318508-373d-46a4-b449-0c6e0057b93f"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "2e80aca8-7ab7-42f7-8445-73f24650c88c",
        "tool_call_id": "call_qw4clN1fhE0VxsEoLpLXB2Y0",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table into table `J09B_temp` for records where the tour starts with `J09B`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09B_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type:\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`\n\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`. Join with `NET_MASTER` and `SALES_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use net data customer table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09B`. Use these column names when exporting:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached. Use `file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
